# Structured Data (JSON‑LD) — All Sites

Use **schema.org JSON‑LD** and keep it valid JSON (no trailing commas).

## Required schemas

- **Organization**: present sitewide (name, url, logo/image, stable `@id`)
- **WebSite**: present sitewide (publisher references the Organization `@id`)
- **Review**: on broker review pages (`/brokers/*-review/`)
  - `itemReviewed` as `Product` (name, url, image)
  - `reviewRating` (ratingValue, bestRating)
  - `author`/`publisher` (Organization)
  - `datePublished`
  - `reviewBody`
- **FAQPage**: on pages that have an FAQ section (questions + acceptedAnswer)
- **Article / BlogPosting**: on blog-style pages (guides, daily/weekly briefs)
  - `headline`, `description`, `datePublished`, `dateModified`
  - `author`/`publisher` as Organization
  - `mainEntityOfPage` as canonical URL

## Automation

Preferred: keep structured data consistent with:
- `scripts/ensure-structured-data.mjs`

Run after large content/routing changes:
- `scripts/ensure-structured-data.mjs`
- `scripts/ensure-seo-meta.mjs`
- `scripts/generate-sitemaps.mjs`

